FBIS3-29751 "dreas036_i_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 Cambodia Khmer Rouge Attack Position in Battambang BK2302085194 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0400 GMT 23 Feb 94 BK2302085194 Phnom Penh AKP Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] Phnom Penh 23 Feb (AKP) -- Two persons were killed in a clash between government forces and Khmer Rouge guerrillas at Ampil Pram Daeum in Bavel District of Battambang Province on 17 February, according to a military source. At 0500 on that day, some 100 Khmer Rouge soldiers attacked for three hours a government position on coordinates [numbers indistinct]. The Khmer Rouge occupied a communal office building, but were repulsed by the government troops a few hours later. An administrative office building, 10 houses, and [words indistinct] belonging to the local people were destroyed in the attack, the source said.
